==Korean==
===Noun===
'''햇무리''' (''haesmuri, haemmuri'')
# [[halo]] around the sun

====Alternative spellings====
*해무리 (''haemuri'') (obsolete)
*햇모로 (''haesmoro, haemmoro'') (obsolete)
*[[햇물]] (''haesmul, haemmul'') (abridged) cf. Japanese [[日]] ([[ひ]], ''hi'') "[[sun]]", German ''[[Himmel]]'' "[[sky]]" (Both Germanic words are said to originally mean "cloud cover", hence probably more chances of halos as an outstanding metapor for the sky.)

====Synonyms====
*[[햇귀엣골]] (''haesgwiesgol'') literally, ring at the sun's ear 
*[[해귀엿골]] (''haegwiyeosgol'') (alternative spelling) cf. [[w:sunwheel|sunwheel]]
*훼여골 (''hwe-yeo-gol'') (supposed older and simpler) cf. Old English ''[[hweogol]]'' "[[wheel]]"

====Antonyms====
*[[달무리]] (''dalmuri'') [[halo]] around the moon
 
====Related terms====
*[[고리]] (''gori'') [[ring]], [[circle]]
*[[골]] (''gol'') (abridged) [[ring]], [[circle]]
*[[무리]] (''muri'') [[halo]], [[ring]], [[circle]]
*[[해]] (''hae'') [[sun]]
*[[햇귀]] (''haesgwi'') (literally, "sun's ear") [[solar ray]] (usually early in the morning)
*[[햇바퀴]] (''haesbakwi'') [[sunwheel]], [[w:sunwheel]]
*[[햇바회]] (''haesbahoe'') (obsolete) [[sunwheel]]

